\ncumulates depleted in incompatible elements can be produced from common\nmid-ocean ridge basaltic melts modified by reaction with hydrated lithospheric\nperidotite. We established that the rate of assimilation of serpentinized\nperidotite is controlled by silica diffusion in the reacting hydrous basaltic\nmelt.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2020 10:25:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-09"}
